Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper deals with sentiment and emotion analysis using multi-modal inputs, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses visual frames as one of the modal inputs for emotion analysis, which falls under the domain of computer vision. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multi-modal sentiment and emotion analysis, which falls under the domain of multimedia. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a deep multi-task learning framework for sentiment and emotion analysis, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a context-level inter-modal attention framework for predicting sentiment and emotions, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
